@startuml
title AI Agent Bridge - Media Flow (Sequence Diagram)\nWindows VM Architecture

actor "Host (User)" as Host
participant "PlanetKitMeetingArea\n(User's Browser)" as UI
participant "Windows Azure VM\n(server-windows.js)" as WinVM
participant "HeadlessAgentPage\n(Chrome on VM)" as Bridge
participant "AudioWorklet\n(PCM Processor)" as Worklet
participant "Gemini AI\n(Google)" as Gemini
participant "Planet Server\n(Conference)" as Planet
actor "Other Participants" as Others

== Initialization ==
Host -> UI: Click AI Agent Invite Button
UI -> WinVM: POST /join-as-agent\n{ roomId, language, voice }
WinVM -> Bridge: puppeteer.launch(headless:false)\nnavigate /headless-agent?roomId=...
Bridge -> Planet: joinConference()\nas AI_HEADLESS_{roomId}
Bridge -> Gemini: WebSocket Connect (v1beta)
Bridge -> WinVM: window.agentConnected = true
WinVM -> UI: { success: true }
UI -> Host: "AI Agent Active" (button dimmed)

== Path 1: Room Audio → AI (Capturing) ==
Host -> Planet: Microphone Input (WebRTC)
Planet -> Bridge: Room Audio Stream\n(PlanetKit captureStream)
Bridge -> Worklet: Process Audio (16kHz PCM16)
Worklet -> Gemini: WebSocket: realtimeInput (Chunks)
Gemini -> Gemini: Multimodal Inference

== Path 2: AI → Conference (Broadcasting) ==
Gemini -> Bridge: WebSocket: serverContent (Audio Data\nFloat32Array)
Bridge -> Bridge: Web Audio API\n(AudioContext 24kHz)
Bridge -> Bridge: Connect to\nMediaStreamDestination
Bridge -> Planet: setCustomMediaStream(aiStream)
Planet -> Others: Broadcast AI Voice (WebRTC)
Planet -> Host: AI Voice (WebRTC)

== Mode Switching (Listen / Respond) ==

note over Host, Gemini
  Dual Safety Net: Gemini text instruction + audio output gate
  Audio input continues even in Listen mode (to maintain context)
  Only the inviter (Host) can toggle modes
end note

Host -> UI: Toggle → Listen Mode
UI -> WinVM: POST /agent-mode\n{ roomId, mode: "listen" }
WinVM -> Bridge: page.evaluate(setAgentMode("listen"))
Bridge -> Bridge: aiAgentService.setMode("listen")\n→ audio output gate ON
Bridge -> Gemini: clientContent:\n"You are now in LISTEN-ONLY mode.\nDo NOT speak or generate audio."
WinVM -> UI: { success: true, mode: "listen" }
UI -> Host: Badge: "Listen Mode"

... time passes (AI silently absorbs conversation) ...

Host -> Planet: Speaking (WebRTC)
Planet -> Bridge: Room Audio Stream
Bridge -> Worklet: Process Audio (continues)
Worklet -> Gemini: realtimeInput (continues)\n<- continues for context retention
Gemini -> Bridge: Audio response (if any)
Bridge -> Bridge: X gate blocked (listen mode)\n-> no audio output

...

Host -> UI: Toggle → Respond Mode
UI -> WinVM: POST /agent-mode\n{ roomId, mode: "respond" }
WinVM -> Bridge: page.evaluate(setAgentMode("respond"))
Bridge -> Bridge: aiAgentService.setMode("respond")\n→ audio output gate OFF
Bridge -> Gemini: clientContent:\n"Wait until addressed.\nDo NOT summarize what you heard."
WinVM -> UI: { success: true, mode: "respond" }
UI -> Host: Badge: "Respond Mode"

Host -> Planet: "Haemil, summarize what we discussed"
Planet -> Bridge: Room Audio
Bridge -> Worklet: Process Audio
Worklet -> Gemini: realtimeInput
Gemini -> Bridge: AI Response (with full context)
Bridge -> Planet: setCustomMediaStream()\n-> broadcast AI response to entire room
Planet -> Host: AI Voice
Planet -> Others: AI Voice

== Session End ==
alt 5-min timeout
  Bridge -> Gemini: Farewell message
  Gemini -> Bridge: AI farewell audio
  Bridge -> Planet: Broadcast farewell
  Bridge -> WinVM: Session cleanup
  WinVM -> WinVM: browser.close()
else Room becomes empty (30s)
  Bridge -> Planet: leaveConference()
  WinVM -> WinVM: browser.close()
else Host clicks Kick button
  UI -> WinVM: POST /disconnect-agent\n{ roomId }
  WinVM -> WinVM: browser.close()
  WinVM -> UI: { success: true }
end

@enduml